@node 08066.011
Subject: Re: 64 Mo problem
From: Hans-Joerg Frieden <hfrieden@uni-trier.de>
Date: Tue, 1 Feb 2000 13:32:43 +0000 (GMT)

Hi!

I agree that a minimum of 64 MB is quite a lot for Amigas. However, there
is technically not even the remotest chance to get memory usage for our
games below 32 MB. Even 64 MB's is a tight fit. We're aware of that,
however, it is our hope that people will ugrade their machines.

Perhaps they won't do it for Heretic II when it comes out. They might
think about it when Shogo is released. They should have done it when SiN
appears (yes, since it already is common knowledge, we are doing it :) 64
MB is the bare minimum today in a machine that does not have support for
virtual memory (at least not on the PPC side, and the 68k side VMM is
useless here), at least when you want to play games like the above.

We definately hope that our games will be reason enough for people to get
more memory; to further advance the minimum hardware platform in the Amiga
sector is one of our goals.

Regards, Hans-Joerg.

