How would you do that ? There are some issues which are completely out of
reach of the library, for instance there is no way to check if bitmap
cache is switched on. 

> warp3d.library could also require some minimal versions of cgx-libraries, it
> could also check for cgx-configurations if bitmap-cache is on, etc.

No way. How would you do that. There's no guarantee that there even *is* a
bitmap cache. If Warp3D runs under Picasso, there's no switch to turn it
off. And if CGX 4.3 handles it's tooltypes differently ? Also, we don't
want to lock out CGX 3 users, so why require a minimal version of the libs
?

> This would remove the difficulties on the different amiga-environments.
> So maybe it will be easier to install a 3D-game on Amiga.

The problems would still be there, only moved to another position, and
completely out of the reach of the end user.

If you drop the ENV variable, what would you get ? To still be
customizable, you would have to write a configuration file. There's no
difference between ENV variables, and a configuration file, only the ENV
variables should be considered more transparent.

