On 11-Feb-00, you wrote:

>First of all, ' i don't understood how gouraud shading works ,i believe
>that the software color the face using the color of vertex in 3DW_Tringle,

You have to do a W3D_SetState(context, W3D_GOURAUD, W3D_ENABLE);
and have texturemapping disabled.
Then you have to set r, g, b and a in your 3 W3D_Triangle structures to
whatever value you want. Then it should work. Remember to set A to 1, else
there is a chance that nothing gets drawed.

>but.......... NO 
>Second, can someone explain the Blending Mode ?

Well, it's simple. In 32-bits display, the last 8 bits are used for a socalled
'Alpha Channel', which contains the 'weight' of the pixel. So when you draw a
pixel on the screen, the alphavalue of the screen pixel and the pixel you want
to draw are compared and blended.

