Sure, have a look at the source code :)

More complex answer:
It uses gouraud shading together with texture mapping. You just have to
set the color value in the vertex structure to some apporpriate value.
Then, you change these values over time, according to some function. For
example, the engine demo uses a 1 second interval: When the interval
starts, the values are set to all red, and with every following frame,
that value gets decremented by some value (this *should* be chosen
accoridng to the elapsed time, but engine doesn't do that to keep it
simple). That's more or less what you'll have to do....

Of course, if you want to just give a position of a light source and have
everything else illuminated according to that, that's a completely
different story, and on that can't be answered with less than 1000 lines
