On Mon, 21 Feb 2000, Dave Cole wrote:

> What's wrong with V2.0 of P96?  Have you mentioned it to the authors??  The
> reason I ask, is due to the hopefully imminent release of the Paraglide.

There seem to be some changes in the internal ModeID that P96 uses. We
use  this info to  determine what  chip is  available, but  since this
changes, W3D will always say "no chip here" and you will get a "ModeID
not found" error... 

We're  working on  it, and  this will  be fixed  when the  Voodoo gets
out... 

Regards, Hans-Joerg.

