> why not ask what resolution as well. I never run my PermediaII in 32bit mode
> (there is no point) a hires screen with 32bits would mean not much free
> memory left on the PermII card

With MiniGL,  the application  says what resolution  it would  like to
have (or it  specifies a ModeID, in which  case the default dimensions
are used), but in window mode, there  is no such thing as a ModeID, so
the bitmap is  allocated as a friend to the  default public screen. If
that's 32 bits, then the bitmap  will most likely also be 32 bits, and
since the W3D_CreateContext  seem to work, it should  work as a whole,
unless of  course Phase5 went  for the chip  ram chips and there  is a
timing problem... :/

