There are  limitiations of the  hardware that you cannot  overcome. No
matter what Wolf  Dietrich wanted you to believe,  the Permedia2 is by
all means an outdated chip that  is even slower than the Voodoo I. You
cannot get  more than about 25 FPS  in 640x480, due to  the nature the
Quake (and  Quake 2 Engines)  work, this is  a limitation of  the fill
rate. But  at least,  you *can*  play in 640x480,  plus have  the neat
things like texture filtering, better light effects etc... 

Actually, for  Heretic II the ViRGE  HW version ran a  bit slower than
the software rendered version on my overclocked 060, and the Permedia2
is somewhere inbetween  the Voodoo I and the ViRGE  (ok, closer to the
Voodoo :)

