@node 08089.019
Subject: GLQuake with 32mb ram, 50-100% speed increase
From: Mark Olsen <BIGFoot@Private.dk>
Date: Thu, 24 Feb 2000 00:22:09 +0100

Hi there.

I finally made GLQuake run with 32 mb ram, 30,9 mb free after boot. Here is
some tips:

Disable EVERYTHING in startup-sequence/user-startup. Every byte is needed.
Put env on disk.
Make WB display on an AGA screen.
Remove all things from wbstartup.
Decrease all hd buffers to ~20.
Disable df0: and cc0: if you use a1200.
Go to your Quake dir and edit id1/autoexec.cfg. Put a "map dm4" in the bottom,
without qoutes.

And start quake like this:

stack 300000         ; I know the author recommends 500000, but this works
just fine.
GLQuakeWOS >nil: -mem 6 -buf 2 -diter off -nosound -nocdaudio -nonetwork

It might crash the first couple of times while "meshing" some models.

Increasing the speed:
On my machine(A1200 200mhz 603e) the GL version is faster than the software
version. And i have only tried the GL version in 320x240, as i am a little low
on memory ATM.
Here is a couple of settings to put into autoexec.cfg or type in manually:

gl_affinemodels 1
gl_cull 0
gl_keepjunctions 1 (might be zero, can't remember).
gl_videosync 0
gl_ztrick 1

Also, try using r_wateralpha 0.2 and stand still in front of a teleporter =).

I've also made GLQuake fail in uploading textures, which sure did produce some
good looking pictures, i will put them online later.

Ciao!

