>library which should basically do the job right for
>all drives, but which apparently doesn't.

Before giving up, there are several things to try.  First, unless you
do the full install, you won't get any music while playing intro
MPEGs.  That's because it can't play an MPEG from the CDROM
simultaneously while playing an audio track from the CDROM.  So the
MPEG must be on hard disk for music, i.e, you must do a full install.

There are several more suggestions in the Wipeout 2097 documentation.
For example, you can set an environment variable so Wipeout 2097 won't
use the cdplayer.library change-volume command.  The cdplayer.library
change-volume command fails with some controller/drive combinations.

You can test independently whether cdplayer.library works with your
system.  There are CLI utilities in the cdplayer.library drawer for
that, or you can download and try any program that uses
cdplayer.library from Aminet.

Also make sure the audio outputs from the CDROM drive are correctly
wired to an amplifier (or mixer) and speakers, and that the volume
control on the front of the drive is turned up!
